

SRTStreamer

REST API Endpoints:

/start-stream: Initiates streaming of a video/audio file. Supports:
Specifying a URL to download the file.
Randomly selecting a file from a predefined directory if no URL is provided.
Setting a maximum number of concurrent streams (up to 10).
/stop-stream/{stream_id}: Stops a specific streaming session using the provided stream_id.
/stream-status/{stream_id}: Retrieves the current status of a specified streaming session, including download progress and streaming status.
File Downloading: Automatically downloads media files from provided URLs before streaming them.

Concurrency Management: Utilizes background threads to manage file downloads and streaming processes without blocking API responses.

